New Records: Matt Olson tied the Braves' single-season home run record with 51 home runs in 2023.
Matt Olson leads the majors in home runs and RBIs this season.
Key Match Events: Matt Olson's record-tying home run in the fourth inning tied the game 1-1 and led to the Braves' eventual 7-6 win in 10 innings.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The home run marked a significant milestone in Braves' history, tying the franchise record set by Andruw Jones in 2005.
